text.section:
This section does not apply to:
a passenger on a railroad vehicle;
an individual who enters railroad property in an emergency to:
rescue from harm another individual or an animal, including livestock, a pet, or wildlife; or
remove an object that the individual reasonably believes to pose an imminent threat to life or limb;
an individual on the station grounds or in the depot of a railroad carrier as a passenger or to transact lawful business;
a person, a family member or invitee of a person, or an employee or independent contractor of a person who enters a railroad right-of-way to obtain access to land that the person owns, leases, or operates at a private crossing approved by the railroad carrier;
a person having permission of the railroad carrier to enter the railroad property;
a law enforcement officer, firefighter, or emergency response personnel while performing official duties;
a representative of the Maryland Department of Transportation or the Department of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation while performing official duties; or
a representative of the Federal Railroad Administration or the National Transportation Safety Board while performing official duties.
